                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18171203-23-off136 t18171203-23-crimeloc139"></join>; the bag of rice was at the door.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. Two men made me drunk; they said they would give me a job to carry a parcel - I fell asleep - They awoke me, and said, it was time to go, and took me to St. John's-street, and put it on my shoulder-the keys must have been put in my pocket.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 42.</p>
               <p>Of <rs id="t18171203-23-verdict140" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18171203-23-verdict140" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18171203-23-verdict140" type="verdictSubcategory" value="lesserOffence"></interp>
               Stealing, but not privately
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Transported for Seven Years.</p>
               <p>Second Middlesex Jury, before Mr. Baron Garrow.</p>
